The paper deals with the problem of recovering a sparse matrix from a matrix sketch, which is a problem in signal processing and information theory. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of compressive sensing theory, which is a popular topic in machine learning and statistics, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The paper also involves matrix operations and algorithms, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Finally, the paper discusses the computational efficiency of the algorithms, which could be considered under cs.SI (Systems and Control).
